            <div>
                <opener><salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>
                <p>I set out for <placeName ref="pl0699">London</placeName> toomorrow therefore beg
                    my queries ab<hi rend="superscript">t.</hi> the Macgregors may be sent to me
                        there.<note type="editorial">See Pennant's letters to Paton on 3<hi rend="superscript">rd</hi> and 11<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> February
                        1776 and Paton's replies of 21<hi rend="superscript">st</hi> and 25<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> March.</note> if anything from <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Low</persName> let it come to me
                    only with passing throâ€™ other hands for I shall take it very ill to have
                    anything anticipated after all my expences &amp; pains. Please to inclose to
                        <persName ref="pe0015">Sir Roger Mostyn Bar<hi rend="superscript">t.</hi>
                        M.P.</persName>
                    <placeName ref="pl0734">Bruton street</placeName>.</p>
                <closer><salute>I am <lb/>D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Sir <lb/>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> obed<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi></salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant</persName></signed>
                <dateline><placeName ref="pl0001">Downing</placeName> March 10<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1776.</dateline></closer>
            </div>
